{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_93","type":"agent_message","text":"The repository rules explain the shape of the problem: metadata bundles here can only carry JSON reachability entries, not `native-image.properties`. `netty-buffer` 4.2.1 already ships upstream runtime-init hints for `AdaptiveByteBufAllocator` and related classes, but those hints are not being picked up in this TCK path, which is why the allocator is still failing after the metadata file exists. I’m reading the existing `netty-common` test build now to see whether the right fix in this repo is to mirror those runtime-init args in the library test config while keeping the metadata JSON scoped and clean."}}
